      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To achieve spinal neutrality, pull your navel in toward your spine and imagine pushing your lower back flat against the floor as if you were trying to stand up from a seated position. This tightens your core like a corset, locking your vertebrae together so your torso remains upright rather than leaning forward excessively. By bracing your abs before the lift, you transfer the pressure to your large muscle groups (glutes and legs) rather than compressing sensitive spinal discs.",
